# ===== Generated Code =====

# OpenAPI Generator temporary files
.openapi-generator/
.openapi-generator-ignore

# ===== OPTION 1: Commit Generated Code (RECOMMENDED WITH CI) =====
# The CI/CD pipeline automatically regenerates and commits API code.
# This provides:
# - Easier onboarding (no generation needed locally)
# - Clear diffs when API changes
# - Faster local builds
# Keep these lines COMMENTED to commit generated code:

# backend/target/generated-sources/
# frontend/src/app/generated/

# ===== OPTION 2: Regenerate on Every Build =====
# If you prefer to regenerate locally and not commit generated code,
# UNCOMMENT the lines below:

# Backend generated sources
# backend/target/generated-sources/
# backend/src/main/java/com/example/taskmanager/api/
# backend/src/main/java/com/example/taskmanager/model/

# Frontend generated code
# frontend/src/app/generated/

# NOTE: If you choose Option 2, remove the "Commit and push generated code"
# step from .github/workflows/ci-cd.yml

